  "synopsis": "\"Lupin III: Secret File\" is actually a compilation of two previously unreleased pilot films; original Cinemascope version from year 1969 and restyled, and redubbed TV version from year 1971. As well as four film trailers. The trailers are for the first four Lupin films: \"Lupin vs. the Clone\", \"Castle of Cagliostro\", \"Legend of the Gold of Babylon\" and \"The Fuma Conspiracy\".\nLater in 1989 \"Lupin III: Secret File 2 - Sound Collection\" was released consisting of openings and endings of all previous Lupin series and theme songs.",
